comments.message:
I'm not sure the recommended coding style in upstream bmcweb.
Wouldn't this be better to be written as follows?

1)
```
#ifndef BMCWEB_INSECURE_DISABLE_AUTHX
            if (userSession != nullptr)
#else
            if(true)
#endif // BMCWEB_INSECURE_DISABLE_AUTHX
```

OR
2)
```
#ifndef BMCWEB_INSECURE_DISABLE_AUTHX
            if (userSession != nullptr)
            {
                cancelDeadlineTimer();
            }
#else
            cancelDeadlineTimer();
#endif // BMCWEB_INSECURE_DISABLE_AUTHX
```

OR 
3) if cancelDeadlineTimer() can be called multiple times,
```
            if (userSession != nullptr)
            {
                cancelDeadlineTimer();
            }

#ifdef BMCWEB_INSECURE_DISABLE_AUTHX
            // Ensure to cancel deadline timer under insecure auth 
            cancelDeadlineTimer();
#endif // BMCWEB_INSECURE_DISABLE_AUTHX
```
